52
00:04:02.180 --> 00:04:03.720
Yes, ma'am!

53
00:04:06.350 --> 00:04:07.730
Hey, Lilith!

54
00:04:07.730 --> 00:04:09.400
What are you doing?

55
00:04:09.400 --> 00:04:12.110
Can it, Shaka! I'm just
doing what I always do!

56
00:04:12.110 --> 00:04:13.900
Plundering again?!

57
00:04:13.900 --> 00:04:16.070
Have some pride as a scientist!

58
00:04:16.070 --> 00:04:18.400
Pride won't fund our research!

59
00:04:18.780 --> 00:04:20.360
Who is she talking to?

60
00:04:20.360 --> 00:04:22.330
Don't get all high and mighty with me!

61
00:04:22.740 --> 00:04:25.200
They won't surrender.

62
00:04:25.200 --> 00:04:26.870
Those are the Straw Hat Pirates.

63
00:04:26.870 --> 00:04:29.000
Their captain was just named an Emperor.

64
00:04:29.000 --> 00:04:30.250
I know, right?!

65
00:04:31.420 --> 00:04:34.750
An Emperor must be rolling in treasure!

66
00:04:35.340 --> 00:04:37.720
In that case, you've made a grave error.

67
00:04:38.840 --> 00:04:39.680
An error?

68
00:04:40.050 --> 00:04:42.430
The sea beasts have them surrounded!

69
00:04:42.430 --> 00:04:43.510
There's no way out!

70
00:04:43.510 --> 00:04:46.470
No, you underestimated them.

71
00:04:46.470 --> 00:04:48.890
Look at the swordsman on the ship.

72
00:04:49.560 --> 00:04:56.030
That's Pirate Hunter Zoro,
a man worth 1 billion 111 million berries.

73
00:04:56.030 --> 00:05:01.490
He's calm because he knows he can
kill you in an instant from there.

74
00:05:02.320 --> 00:05:06.160
Same goes for the woman behind him, 
Devil Child Nico Robin.

75
00:05:06.160 --> 00:05:10.500
And just how in the world could they
beat this many sea beast weapons?!

76
00:05:10.500 --> 00:05:14.630
The strong can deduce
which targets to prioritize!

77
00:05:14.630 --> 00:05:16.750
You're the one who's in trouble.

78
00:05:16.750 --> 00:05:18.710
So those whippersnappers...

79
00:05:18.710 --> 00:05:20.170
are decoys?!
– Cool!
– Cool!

80
00:05:20.550 --> 00:05:21.880
I let my guard down!

81
00:05:22.760 --> 00:05:24.350
Hey, Vegapunk!

82
00:05:25.050 --> 00:05:27.310
We have some demands
you're going to meet...

83
00:05:28.310 --> 00:05:29.520
Got it?

84
00:05:29.520 --> 00:05:33.270
A-Are you trying to threaten me?!

85
00:05:33.270 --> 00:05:34.270
That's fine.

86
00:05:34.270 --> 00:05:35.520
Bring them here.

87
00:05:35.520 --> 00:05:38.530
I'm interested in that crew.

88
00:05:38.530 --> 00:05:42.240
Shaka the Just

89
00:05:44.740 --> 00:05:46.530
Have you been here before?

90
00:05:46.530 --> 00:05:50.120
Yeah, when I was a kid.
Back then, it was just an ordinary lab.

91
00:05:50.120 --> 00:05:53.210
And why'd you come back?

92
00:05:54.290 --> 00:05:57.040
You said you had business with Vegapunk...

93
00:05:57.040 --> 00:05:58.710
Depending on his answer...

94
00:05:59.130 --> 00:06:00.800
he may have to die!

95
00:06:02.050 --> 00:06:03.840
Hold on a second!

96
00:06:05.600 --> 00:06:07.140
What happened?!

97
00:06:07.680 --> 00:06:09.600
My dad...

98
00:06:09.600 --> 00:06:12.560
Vegapunk turned him into a cyborg.

99
00:06:12.560 --> 00:06:14.730
A cyborg?! That's so cool!

100
00:06:14.730 --> 00:06:16.690
Screw you!

101
00:06:18.150 --> 00:06:21.740
At this point, he's lost all sense of humanity...

102
00:06:22.650 --> 00:06:24.700
He doesn't even know who he is...

103
00:06:26.820 --> 00:06:29.240
He's become nothing more
than a living weapon.

104
00:06:29.830 --> 00:06:32.660
That is truly awful...

105
00:06:33.870 --> 00:06:36.420
It is, and I'm gonna make him pay.

106
00:06:36.710 --> 00:06:38.630
I'm really sorry, Bogey!

107
00:06:39.380 --> 00:06:41.260
Bo-nn-ey!

108
00:06:42.010 --> 00:06:43.550
I'm sorry, Bonney!

109
00:06:44.800 --> 00:06:46.140
Just climb!

110
00:06:46.140 --> 00:06:48.070
I think we can get to the surface from here.

111
00:06:48.600 --> 00:06:49.640
Okay!

112
00:06:55.100 --> 00:06:56.980
Oh! We're almost there!

113
00:06:56.980 --> 00:06:58.060
I'm so excited!

114
00:06:58.560 --> 00:07:02.150
Wait for me, food!

115
00:07:03.740 --> 00:07:05.740
